@startuml
title Batch A Parent Issue Progress, Documents, And Deliverables (2026-03-17)

skinparam backgroundColor transparent
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultTextAlignment left

package "Current Squadrail Surfaces" {
  [IssueDetail\nsubtask progress] as CurrentProgress
  [Attachments] as CurrentAttachments
  [ChangeReviewDesk\nverification/diff artifacts] as CurrentChangeSurface
  [Protocol Messages\nwith artifacts] as CurrentProtocol
  [Knowledge Documents] as CurrentKnowledge
}

package "Reference Patterns" {
  [IssueDocumentsSection UI] as RefUI
  [documents.ts service] as RefService
  [issue_documents + document_revisions] as RefDb
}

package "Batch A Target" {
  [IssueProgressSnapshot] as ProgressSnapshot
  [Issue Documents API] as DocumentsApi
  [Issue Documents UI] as DocumentsUi
  [Deliverables Read Model] as Deliverables
}

package "Delivery Surfaces" {
  [Overview] as Overview
  [Work] as Work
  [IssueDetail] as IssueDetail
}

CurrentProgress --> ProgressSnapshot : promote current logic
CurrentProtocol --> ProgressSnapshot : phase / role / blockers
CurrentChangeSurface --> ProgressSnapshot : review / qa hints

RefDb --> DocumentsApi
RefService --> DocumentsApi
RefUI --> DocumentsUi
DocumentsApi --> DocumentsUi

CurrentAttachments --> Deliverables
CurrentChangeSurface --> Deliverables
CurrentProtocol --> Deliverables

ProgressSnapshot --> Overview
ProgressSnapshot --> Work
ProgressSnapshot --> IssueDetail

DocumentsUi --> IssueDetail
Deliverables --> IssueDetail

CurrentKnowledge ..> DocumentsApi : do not reuse

note right of CurrentKnowledge
Knowledge documents are immutable
retrieval/ingest artifacts.

Issue documents are mutable
operator-facing working docs.
end note

note bottom of Deliverables
V1 starts as a federated panel:
- attachments
- diff
- approval
- verification artifacts
- latest run/workspace artifacts

No generic artifact registry yet.
end note

note bottom of ProgressSnapshot
Main user question:
"Where is my parent issue now?"
end note

@enduml
